{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow couples not living together to meet indoors during lockdown",
        "additional_details": "Lockdown is an isolating time for all, revoking most freedoms to meet with friends, family and other support networks. For many, their significant other is their only support.\r\n\r\nWe are asking for the government to allow two people in a committed relationship to meet inside, in a private place. \r\n\r\nAlthough a lockdown may be argued as necessary, it is inhumane to prevent two loved ones from being together. By permitting this, there will be greater compliance with the rest of the rules.",
        "background": "The new lockdown rules won't allow those in a committed relationship to meet indoors. \r\n\r\nIt is not always possible to be apart of the same support bubble.\r\n\r\nWe wish for the government to allow those in a committed relationship to meet each other indoors throughout the lockdown period.",
